channel.title: Frostwire
channel.description:
Ok, so today I was pissed off with using Photoshop 7 cause I can't do shit like I could with CS5... So I got on Frostwire and I started a torrent. Well, it got done and I don't think it was a virus cause Avast picks up viruses from Frostwire and it didn't set it off. Went to open the RAR and it said file was corrupt. I was like WTF?!?!?!? So I went back to Frostwire and it said at the bottom: Status: Seeding Seeds: 0/3
What the fuck is a seed...

item.title: Frostwire
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

I get all of my torrents off of thepiratebay. I use BitTorrent as well. And a seeder is what Ziplock said, someone who provides the file for people and helps to increase download speed.

When you are downloading off thepiratebay, be EXTREMELY cautious of files with low seeds. If there is a file with 20-30+ seeds or something, go with it, and scan everything before you run it. Don’t always expect virus scanners to pick it up immediately.
